    "body": "buf is a pointer argument, not a local char array, so sizeof(buf) is just the size of a pointer type on the platform.  This is always an incorrect value, but on 32-bit platforms it actually has an impact, since sizeof(buf) is just 4 and causes the buffer to get truncated.",
